            <a class="open" href="javascript:void(0)">p382 Broken Promise #5 (Garraty helping Art Baker)</a>
            <div style="display:none">
                <p>&ldquo;Walk a little bit longer,&rdquo; Garraty said through his tears. &ldquo;Walk a little longer,
                    Art.&rdquo;<br />&ldquo;No&mdash;I can&rsquo;t.&rdquo;<br />&ldquo;All right.&rdquo;<br />&ldquo;Maybe
                    I&rsquo;ll see you, man,&rdquo; Baker said, and wiped slick blood from his face absently.<br />Garraty
                    lowered his head and wept.<br />&ldquo;Don&rsquo;t watch &rsquo;em do it,&rdquo; Baker said.
                    &ldquo;Promise me that, too.&rdquo;<br />Garraty nodded, beyond speech.<br />&ldquo;Thanks.
                    You&rsquo;ve been my friend, Garraty.&rdquo; Baker tried to smile. He stuck his hand blindly out,
                    and Garraty shook it with both of his.<br />&ldquo;Another time, another place,&rdquo; Baker said.<br />Garraty
                    put his hands over his face and had to bend over to keep walking. The sobs ripped out of him and
                    made him ache with a pain that was far beyond anything the Walk had been able to inflict.<br />He
                    hoped he wouldn&rsquo;t hear the shots. But he did.
                </p>
